{"title_page": "Bruce Garvey", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name        = Bruce Garvey\n| image       =\n| caption     =\n| birthname   = Bruce Noble Garvey\n| birth_date  = c. {{Birth date|df=yes|1939|10|17}}\n| birth_place = [[London]], England\n| death_date  = {{death date and age|df=yes|2010|8|1|1939|10|17}}\n| death_place = [[Wellington, Ontario]], Canada\n| education   =\n| occupation  = reporter, editor\n| alias       =\n| title       =\n| family      = \n| spouse      = Celia Wasbrough\n| domestic_partner =\n| children    = Paul Garvey, Danny Garvey, Steven Garvey, Andrea Bucic \n| relatives   = Bonnie Fitzgerald (Daughter In-law), Kyla Garvey (Grand Child), Megan Garvey (Grand Child), Colin Garvey (Grand Child, Liza Valentine (Daughter In-law) Alison McDevitt (Grand Child), Kristen McDevitt (Grand Child)\n| nationality = English\n| years_active= <!-- YYYY \u2013 YYYY -->\n| credits     =\n| agent       =\n| URL         =\n}}\n'''Bruce Noble Garvey''' (c. 1939 &ndash; 1 August 2010) was a British-born Canadian journalist and editor.\n\nBorn in [[London]], England, Garvey moved to Ontario, Canada at age 19 and worked at various newspapers such as the ''Stratford Beacon-Herald''. After jobs at [[United Press International]] and the ''[[The Gazette (Montreal)|Montreal Gazette]]'', he joined the ''[[Toronto Star]]'' in 1967 where he held various editorial and bureau chief positions. In 1977, he moved to broadcast journalism first with [[CBC Television]] where he became a producer for ''[[The Journal (Canadian TV series)|The Journal's]]'' documentaries. He later joined the news department at [[Global Television Network|Global Television]]. He returned to print journalism in 1998 when he became the news editor for ''[[Ottawa Citizen]]'''s weekend editions, and became a columnist for the ''[[National Post]]''.<ref name=OCobit /><ref name=TSobit />\n\nIn 1970, Garvey and ''[[Daily Express]]'''s Richard Killian were the only reporters present at [[Christopher C. Kraft Jr. Mission Control Center|NASA's Mission Control]] when the crew of [[Apollo 13]] first reported the critical equipment failures which changed the lunar mission into a rescue operation.\n\nIn May 2009, Garvey was diagnosed with [[lung cancer]] and died in [[Wellington, Ontario]] on 1 August 2010.<ref name=OCobit>{{cite news |url=https://ottawacitizen.com/news/Bruce+Garvey+1939+2010+great+journalists+generation/3350248/story.html |title=Bruce Garvey (1939-2010): 'One of the great journalists of his generation' |first=Glen |last=McGregor |newspaper=[[Ottawa Citizen]] |date=2 August 2010 |accessdate=2 August 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100824023733/http://www.ottawacitizen.com/news/Bruce%2BGarvey%2B1939%2B2010%2Bgreat%2Bjournalists%2Bgeneration/3350248/story.html |archivedate=24 August 2010 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref name=TSobit>{{cite news | url=https://www.thestar.com/article/842968--bruce-garvey-70-a-classic-newspaperman | title=Bruce Garvey, 70: A classic newspaperman | first=Brendan | last=Kennedy | newspaper=[[Toronto Star]] | date=1 August 2010 | accessdate=2 August 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/thestar/obituary.aspx?n=bruce-noble-garvey&pid=144447041 | title=Obituary: Bruce Noble Garvey | publisher=[[Toronto Star]]/Legacy.com | date=3 August 2010 | accessdate=4 August 2010 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite news | url=https://ottawacitizen.com/life/Archival+story+Recalling+rescue+Apollo/2783755/story.html | title=Recalling the rescue of Apollo 13 | first=Bruce | last=Garvey | date=3 February 2003 | newspaper=[[Ottawa Citizen]] | accessdate=2 August 2010 }}\n\ns\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garvey, Bruce}}\n[[Category:1939 births]]\n[[Category:2010 deaths]]\n[[Category:Canadian newspaper editors]]\n[[Category:Canadian male journalists]]\n[[Category:Canadian television journalists]]\n[[Category:Deaths fr