ditions, and became a columnist for the ''[[National Post]]''.<ref name=OCobit /><ref name=TSobit />\n\nIn 1970, Garvey and ''[[Daily Express]]'''s Richard Killian were the only reporters present at [[Christopher C. Kraft Jr. Mission Control Center|NASA's Mission Control]] when the crew of [[Apollo 13]] first reported the critical equipment failures which changed the lunar mission into a rescue operation.\n\nIn May 2009, Garvey was diagnosed with [[lung cancer]] and died in [[Wellington, Ontario]] on 1 August 2010.<ref name=OCobit>{{cite news |url=https://ottawacitizen.com/news/Bruce+Garvey+1939+2010+great+journalists+generation/3350248/story.html |title=Bruce Garvey (1939-2010): 'One of the great journalists of his generation' |first=Glen |last=McGregor |newspaper=[[Ottawa Citizen]] |date=2 August 2010 |accessdate=2 August 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100824023733/http://www.ottawacitizen.com/news/Bruce%2BGarvey%2B1939%2B2010%2Bgreat%2Bjournalists%2Bgeneration/3350248/story.html |archivedate=24 August 2010 |df=dmy }}</ref><ref name=TSobit>{{cite news | url=https://www.thestar.com/article/842968--bruce-garvey-70-a-classic-newspaperman | title=Bruce Garvey, 70: A classic newspaperman | first=Brendan | last=Kennedy | newspaper=[[Toronto Star]] | date=1 August 2010 | accessdate=2 August 2010 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/thestar/obituary.aspx?n=bruce-noble-garvey&pid=144447041 | title=Obituary: Bruce Noble Garvey | publisher=[[Toronto Star]]/Legacy.com | date=3 August 2010 | accessdate=4 August 2010 }}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{cite news | url=https://ottawacitizen.com/life/Archival+story+Recalling+rescue+Apollo/2783755/story.html | title=Recalling the rescue of Apollo 13 | first=Bruce | last=Garvey | date=3 February 2003 | newspaper=[[Ottawa Citizen]] | accessdate=2 August 2010 }}\n\ns\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garvey, Bruce}}\n[[Category:1939 births]]\n[[Category:2010 de